			    STPJS 323</div>
  <p class="cont">Son of Man;<span class="footRef">1</span> so Melchizedek ordained Abraham<span class="footRef">2</span> and sent him away. Abraham rejoiced, saying,
  Now I have a priesthood.</p>
  <div class="topic">The Mission of Elijah</div>
  <p class="std">Salvation<span class="footRef">3</span> could not come to the world without the mediation of Jesus Christ.<span class="footRef">4</span></p>
  <p class="std">How shall God come to the rescue<span class="footRef">5</span> of this generation? He will send Elijah the prophet.<span class="footRef">6</span> The law
  revealed to Moses in Horeb never was revealed to the children of Israel as a nation.<span class="footRef">7</span> Elijah shall
  reveal the covenants<span class="footRef">8</span> to seal the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the children to the fathers.<span class="footRef">9</span></p>
  <p class="std">The anointing and sealing is to be called, elected and made sure.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <p class="std">&ldquo;Without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning of days nor end of
  life, but made like unto the Son of God, abideth a priest continually.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">11</span> The Melchizedek Priesthood
  holds the right from the eternal God,<span class="footRef">12</span> and not by descent from father and mother; and that
  priesthood is as eternal<span class="footRef">13</span> as God Himself,<span class="footRef">14</span> having neither beginning of days nor end of life.</p>
  <p class="std">The 2nd Priesthood is Patriarchal authority.<span class="footRef">15</span> Go to and finish the temple, and God will fill it
  with power,<span class="footRef">16</span> and you will then receive more knowledge concerning this priesthood.<span class="footRef">17</span></p>
  <p class="std">The 3rd is what is called the Levitical Priesthood, consisting of priests to administer in outward
  ordinances,<span class="footRef">18</span> made without an oath; but the Priesthood of Melchizedek is by an oath and covenant.<span class="footRef">19</span></p>
  <p class="std">The Holy Ghost is God&rsquo;s messenger<span class="footRef">20</span> to administer in all those priesthoods.<span class="footRef">21</span></p>
  <p class="std">Jesus Christ is the heir of this Kingdom<span class="footRef">22</span>&mdash;the Only Begotten of the Father<span class="footRef">23</span> according to the
  flesh,<span class="footRef">24</span> and holds the keys over all this world.<span class="footRef">25</span></p>
  <p class="std">Men have to suffer that they may come upon Mount Zion<span class="footRef">26</span> and be exalted above the heavens.<span class="footRef">27</span></p>
  <p class="std">I know a man that has been caught up to the third heavens,<span class="footRef">28</span> and can say, with Paul, that we
  have seen and heard things that are not lawful to utter.<span class="footRef">29</span> (Aug. 27, 1843.) DHC 5:554–556.</p>
  <div class="topic">Instructions Respecting Plurality of Wives</div>
